        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 23 at 8:54PM EDT by NWS Columbia SC</headline>
        <description>At 853 PM EDT, the public reported a strong thunderstorm near Dreher
Island State Park, or 9 miles northwest of Highway 6 at Lake Murray
Dam, moving northwest at 5 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Public.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Chapin, Melvin Park, and Little Mountain.

This includes Interstate 26 near mile marker 88.
</description>
        <instruction>Dime sized hail was recently reported near Chapin. If outdoors,
consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
